article.headline: Arkansas 80, Texas Southern 61
article.story: FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. -- Jason Henry returned from a suspension to score 19 points, and Arkansas easily defeated Texas Southern 80-61 Wednesday night. Rotnei Clarke scored 16 points and Michael Sanchez added 10 for the Razorbacks, who went on a 24-5 run in the first half and weren't threatened after that. Henry and Montrell McDonald were each suspended for Saturday's win over Florida A&M. McDonald didn't play against Texas Southern, but Henry did and was a factor throughout. Courtney Fortson added 11 assists for Arkansas (5-1). Henry, Clarke, Sanchez and Fortson are all freshmen playing significant minutes for the Razorbacks. DeAndre Hall led Texas Southern (0-7) with 19 points. Texas Southern coach Tony Harvey was ejected with 9:31 remaining in the first half after a second technical foul.
